According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Europe Solid State Transformers (SST) market was valued at USD 115.8 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 143.2 million in 2025 to USD 487.6 million by 2032, registering a robust CAGR of 19.1% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing rapid expansion as European countries accelerate investments in smart grid modernization, renewable energy integration, and electric mobility infrastructure. The growing adoption of advanced power electronic transformers capable of bidirectional power flow, voltage regulation, and enhanced grid stability is creating significant growth opportunities across utilities, transportation, and industrial sectors.
